The paper focuses on Interactive Navigation tasks with mobile manipulators, which are commonly studied in the field of Robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses Reinforcement Learning (RL) algorithms, which are also commonly studied in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the benefits of Hierarchical RL (HRL), which is a subfield of RL and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of mobile manipulators also involves control systems and dynamics, which are studied in the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method in 3D environments with physics simulation, which involves computer vision techniques for perception and mapping, studied in the field of Computer Vision (cs.CV).
